      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Testing performed at multiple clinically relevant loading rates and angulation conditions to characterize sensitivity.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted at a single crosshead displacement rate (5 mm/min) and a single screw angulation (0°), consistent with ASTM F1717 but not spanning the range of in vivo loading scenarios. Only one test condition was evaluated, falling short of the required gradation 3 that demands at least two systematically varied conditions. This deficiency was noted but the overall assessment was advanced to High assurance on the basis of favorable QoI agreement metrics, without adequately accounting for the uncharacterized condition sensitivity."
