    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team determined that the FEA modeling framework demonstrates High assurance for the non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending COU. Twelve of thirteen credibility factors met or exceeded required levels. The single shortfall in Test conditions (achievedLevel 2 vs. requiredLevel 3) was considered acceptable given the favorable quantitative agreement across all three QoIs and the use of the standardized ASTM F1717 protocol. The team concluded that the overall evidence base supports a High assurance declaration and the Accepted decision for regulatory submission.",
